paint.viewer.utils

Class RecordingEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • paint.viewer.utils.RecordingEntry

  • public class RecordingEntry
extends Object
    Represents a single recording entry within an experiment. Each RecordingEntry encapsulates metadata, image paths, and adjustable visibility control parameters (e.g., density ratio, variability, and R² threshold).

    Images are preloaded via ImageIO or ImageJ Opener, and associated square data can be lazily fetched and cached from the experiment context.

        Constructs a new RecordingEntry with associated images and control parameters.
        Parameters:
        recording - the underlying Recording metadata
        trackmateImagePath - path to the TrackMate overlay image
        brightfieldImagePath - path to the Brightfield reference image
        experimentName - name of the parent experiment
        minRequiredDensityRatio - minimum required density ratio threshold
        maxAllowableVariability - maximum allowable variability threshold
        minRequiredRSquared - minimum R² value (0.0–1.0)
        neighbourMode - neighbour visibility mode as string
